CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 16, 1954, pg. 6, reads: "Carver Luncheon - The tenth annual observance of George Washington Carver Week was highlighted with a luncheon at the Sheraton Hotel on Wednesday...Some of the principals in luncheon program are shown in the third photo. Left to right: Mrs. Ruth Caston Mueller, speaker; Mrs. I. Oseroff, who presided; Mayor David L. Lawrence, Mrs. Alma Illery, founder and president of the National Achievement Clubs, Inc., which sponsored the celebration, and the Very Rev. Vernon E. Gallagher, president of Duquesne University, who gave the invocation."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, left to right: Ruth Caston Mueller, Mrs. I. Oseroff, Mayor David L. Lawrence, Alma Illery, and Rev. Vernon E. Gallagher, posed behind banquet table in Penn Sheraton Hotel for George Washington Carver luncheon
